alerts.title: High Wind Warning
regions: Coastal North Bay Including Point Reyes National Seashore
East Bay Hills and the Diablo Range
alerts.description:
...STRONG AND GUSTY WINDS EXPECTED THURSDAY EVENING THROUGH
FRIDAY MORNING...
.A potent spring storm system will bring strong and gusty winds
to the the San Francisco Bay Area and Monterey Bay Area beginning
Thursday evening and continuing into Friday morning. The strongest
winds are expected to occur along the coast and in the hills.
Winds will diminish by late Friday morning...but will remain gusty
through Friday night as a second storm system moves through.
...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO
5 AM PDT FRIDAY...
* LOCATION...Coastal North Bay...North Bay Mountains...San
Francisco...San Francisco Peninsula Coast...East Bay
Hills...Santa Cruz Mountains.
* TIMING...Thursday evening through early Friday morning.
Strongest winds will occur Thursday night.
* WINDS...Sustained southerly winds of 30 to 40 MPH are likely
with gusts in excess of 50 MPH.
* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will make driving difficult especially for
drivers of high profile vehicles. Downed trees and powerlines
are also possible during strong winds.

alerts.title: Wind Advisory
alerts.description:
...STRONG AND GUSTY WINDS EXPECTED THURSDAY EVENING THROUGH
FRIDAY MORNING...
.A potent spring storm system will bring strong and gusty winds
to the the San Francisco Bay Area and Monterey Bay Area beginning
Thursday evening and continuing into Friday morning. The strongest
winds are expected to occur along the coast and in the hills.
Winds will diminish by late Friday morning...but will remain gusty
through Friday night as a second storm system moves through.
...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO 5 AM
PDT FRIDAY...
* LOCATION...North Bay Valleys, San Francisco Bay Shoreline and
the East Bay Interior Valleys.
* TIMING...Thursday evening through early Friday morning.
* WINDS...Sustained southerly winds of 20 to 30 MPH are likely
along with gusts in excess of 45 MPH.
* IMPACTS...Strong winds can result in downed trees and powerlines
and could result in local power outages.

alerts.title: Beach Hazards Statement
regions: Coastal North Bay Including Point Reyes National Seashore
Southern Monterey Bay and Big Sur Coast
alerts.description:
...BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM PDT FRIDAY
THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING...
* HAZARDS...LARGE SHORE BREAKS...RIP CURRENTS...AND SNEAKER
WAVES.
* TIMING...FRIDAY MORNING THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING.
* LOCATION...THE COASTLINE FROM NORTHERN SONOMA COUNTY SOUTH
THROUGH SOUTHERN MONTEREY COUNTY. IN PARTICULAR WEST TO
NORTHWEST FACING BEACHES INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO OCEAN
BEACH...MONTARA STATE BEACH...MARINA STATE BEACH...MONTEREY
STATE BEACH...AND ASILOMAR STATE BEACH.
* POTENTIAL IMPACTS...LARGE SHORE BREAKS COULD INJURE
BEACHGOERS. SNEAKER WAVES COULD KNOCK UNSUSPECTING PEOPLE INTO
THE COLD... TURBULENT OCEAN. RIP CURRENTS COULD PULL PEOPLE
OUT TO SEA.
